Third-party components
================================================================================

This project incorporates code from the following upstream projects. Each is
acknowledged below with its origin, license, and (where applicable) a summary
of modifications. Their licenses are reproduced inside the respective
subdirectories where relevant.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
padne — PCB power-delivery-network FEM solver
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Upstream: https://github.com/atx/padne
* License:  GNU General Public License v3.0
* Used by:  pdnsolver/ (modified fork, vendored)
* Status:   Modified fork. See pdnsolver/CHANGES.md for the full list of
            changes relative to upstream and pdnsolver/LICENSE.upstream for
            the upstream GPL-3.0 text. Notable modifications include porting
            the mesher from CGAL to the `triangle` PyPI package, replacing
            PEP 695 generics with TypeVar/Generic for Python 3.11
            compatibility, and adding orphan-vertex guards in the Laplace
            solver.

